## Overview

This folder documents all standalone CTF-style challenges completed on TryHackMe, 
organised by difficulty. Unlike the structured learning paths in this repository, 
challenges are open-ended — no guided instructions, no step-by-step hints. 
You are given a target, and the objective is simple: enumerate, exploit, escalate, 
capture the flag.

Challenges are where learned techniques get pressure-tested. A methodology that 
works cleanly in a guided room often needs adapting when applied to a machine 
that gives nothing away. These rooms build the problem-solving instincts, 
tool fluency, and structured thinking that separate someone who has studied 
security from someone who can actually practise it.

